<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFCFFFC21687FF37FAE558F2" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFCFFFC21687FF37FAE558F2" blockId="23.[151,1436,150,394]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC21687FF37FE8059CB" bold="true" box="[199,338,150,176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC21717FF36FDA159CA" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[343,627,151,177]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albopunctata">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC21717FF36FDA159CA" box="[343,627,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Trachylepis albopunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread species in 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFCFFFC215D5FF36FC3859CA" box="[917,1002,151,177]" name="Angola" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Angola</collectingCountry>
, although it is absent from southeastern regions of the country (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC217E6FF1AFD4659AE" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[422,660,187,213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC21453FF1AFD9C59AE" box="[531,590,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen was presumably offered to Newton by Américo da Costa, as that was the name present in its internal label. 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC214BDFF7EFC4D5982" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[765,927,223,249]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC215E9FF7EFC305981" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[937,994,223,250]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">1906</bibRefCitation>
) did not cite it in any of his publications but identified it as “ 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC21733FEA2FDDE5867" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1895" box="[371,524,259,285]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Mabuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC21733FEA2FDDE5867" box="[371,524,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mabuia varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. The Angolan and Zambian specimens of this species have long been considered to be 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC2169BFE86FE70583B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[219,418,295,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC2169BFE86FE70583B" box="[219,418,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Trachylepis varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC2145CFE86FCE0583A" author="Weinell, J. L. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[540,818,295,321]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="103 - 117" refId="ref40726" refString="Weinell, J. L. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Systematics and phylogeography of the widely distributed african skink Trachylepis varia species complex. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 120, 103 - 117. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2017.11.014" type="journal article" year="2018">Weinell &amp; Bauer (2018)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC215ACFE86FB61583B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1004,1203,295,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="varia">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC215ACFE86FB61583B" box="[1004,1203,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Trachylepis varia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent from both countries. 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC2174CFEEAFE2F581E" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[268,509,331,357]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC21734FEEAFE7E581E" box="[372,428,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
referred to the species as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC2155EFEEAFBEE581E" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[798,1084,331,357]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albopunctata">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC2155EFEEAFBEE581E" box="[798,1084,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Trachylepis albopunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFCFFFC212EFFEEAFA4A581E" author="Weinell, J. L. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Colston, T. J. &amp; Jackman, T. R. &amp; Kuhn, A. &amp; Conradie, W. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1199,1432,331,357]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="183 - 195" refId="ref40781" refString="Weinell, J. L., Branch, W. R., Colston, T. J., Jackman, T. R., Kuhn, A., Conradie, W. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2019) A species-level phylogeny of Trachylepis (Scincidae: Mabuyinae) provides insight into their reproductive mode evolution. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 136, 183 - 195. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2019.04.002" type="journal article" year="2019">
Weinell 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC2134CFEEAFA96581E" box="[1292,1348,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, in a phylogeny study on the genus 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFCFFFC2145DFECEFD7258F2" box="[541,672,367,393]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFCFFFC2145DFECEFD7258F2" box="[541,672,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Trachylepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, followed its usage for Angolan (and Zambian) specimens.
</paragraph>
